This was great - I made two during Passover. One for the seder, and one to have during the week. It was very easy, and a big hit. Plus, it doesn't taste like a passover dish.

Rating: 4
This was the hit of my Passover meal -- absolutely perfect, not too sweet or too tart -- a hit, and easy to make!

Rating: 4
This was a fabulous dessert - made even better by pretty simple preparation. I followed the advice of a previous reviewer and cooked it for only about 30-35 mins. which was adequate. I didn't have 1-1/2 lbs. of rhubarb, only had 2 c.(3 stalks) instead of the called-for 4 c. but I compensated w/ another cup or so of strawberries and it still turned out great. We had it with Haagen-Dazs Vanilla - YUM!

Rating: 4
Absolutely delicious. However, for the topping, I also added 1 cup of granulated white sugar and mixed it with an electric mixer. I also used 1/2 ground almonds (instead of matzah cake meal) for some of the topping and it was FABULOUS! It also needs to cook for less time - otherwise, it comes out too soupy. But every one loves it! It is VERY delicious!

Rating: 4
The kind of recipe that makes me feel like renewing my subscription to Gourmet. I would definitely do this all year-round (and I am planning on it). The texture of the whole dish is great, both crunchy and liquid and the compote has some kick (thanks to the lemon juice). I used frozen strwaberries and may have ended up with more juice than with fresh ones, but I liked it. Enjoy it!